records.addlTxt:
Sentencing hearing proceeded. Statements made as to sentencing.  

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 48 MONTHS, consecutive to case 14CF4855, with credit for 95 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 30 MONTHS.  

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 3 YEARS with the following conditions:
1) No contact with the City Hall Square Apartments at 104 E. Mason Street;
2) Pay restitution in the amount of $370.00 to City Hall Square Apartments. Restitution to be paid FIRST before costs, fees and surcharges;
3) AODA assessment and comply with recommended treatment and counseling;
4) Costs, fees, surcharges, and restitution to be paid during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
5) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge (unless previously submitted);
6) Court ordered 4 MONTHS condition time in the House of Correction, consecutive to case 14CF4855. Defendant may participate in vocational training and other programming;

If revoked, court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds and earnings.

